This paper discusses the development of models for machine consciousness, which is a topic that falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on the application of these models in humanoid robotics (cs.RO). The use of deep learning in replicating human sensory perceptions such as speech recognition and vision suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural networks (cs.NE).
